<p><strong>The Century: America's Time Episode 8: The Best Years (1946-1952)</strong></p>
<p><strong>Question 1:</strong> What was the significance of the Truman Doctrine?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The Truman Doctrine was a policy of American containment of Soviet expansion during the early Cold War. It asserted that the United States would support countries threatened by Soviet communism.</p>
<p><strong>Question 2:</strong> What was the Marshall Plan?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The Marshall Plan was a massive economic aid program provided by the United States to help Western Europe rebuild after World War II. It promoted economic recovery, reduced poverty, and prevented further communist expansion.</p>
<p><strong>Question 3:</strong> What was the Korean War?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The Korean War was a conflict between North Korea, supported by the Soviet Union, and South Korea, supported by the United States. It was one of the first major military confrontations of the Cold War.</p>
<p><strong>Question 4:</strong> What were the "baby boomers"?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The "baby boomers" refer to the generation born during the post-World War II period, between 1946 and 1964. They were characterized by high birth rates and increased prosperity.</p>
<p><strong>Question 5:</strong> What were the major technological innovations of the 1950s?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> The 1950s saw significant technological advancements, including the development of the transistor, the introduction of personal computers, and the first successful nuclear fusion reactions. These innovations had a profound impact on communication, computing, and energy sources.</p>